  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in serious criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Potential prison sentences:\n- Up to 20 years in federal prison per offense\n- Maximum sentences can increase for more complex cases\n- Potential additional time for related criminal activities\n\n2. Financial penalties:\n- Substantial fines, often up to $500,000 or double the value of the funds involved\n- Potential forfeitures of assets connected to laundered funds\n\n3. Additional consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential civil penalties\n- Deportation for non-citizens\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like transaction amount, prior criminal history, and specific circumstances of the offense. Prosecutions are typically handled by federal agencies like the Department of Justice.",
